    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>

    <div class="faq-question">Will my RELX vape definitely set off a fire alarm?</div>
    <div class="faq-answer">Not definitely, but it's possible under certain circumstances, especially if you vape directly near a detector or produce very dense clouds of vapor in a poorly ventilated room.  Normal, moderate vaping is less likely to be an issue.</div>

    <div class="faq-question">What type of smoke detector is most likely to be triggered by vape?</div>
    <div class="faq-answer">Ionization detectors, which are more sensitive to small particles, *might* be slightly more prone to false alarms from vape aerosol compared to photoelectric detectors, which are better at detecting larger smoke particles from smoldering fires. However, both types could potentially be triggered under the right conditions.</div>

    <div class="faq-question">Can I vape indoors if I just blow the vapor away from the detector?</div>
    <div class="faq-answer">While blowing vapor away from the detector helps, it doesn't eliminate the risk entirely, especially in poorly ventilated spaces. It's better to combine this with other strategies like ventilation and moderate vaping for the safest approach.</div>
